    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/188</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-27T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3009. Your 4187, August 3. Your despatch No. 4070, August 6.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d73fn1">Despatch not printed.</note> War and Navy Departments have
                    agreed to make payments to the <pb facs="0129" n="45" xml:id="pg_45"/>
                    categories of officer prisoners of war specified in the proposal of the German
                    Government in accordance with the terms stated therein, pending a definite
                    solution of this matter at the prisoners of war conference at Berne. The
                    Department instructs you to request Spanish Embassy at Berlin to inform German
                    Government to this effect. Advise <persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                    >Garrett</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
